                "url": "/topics/reason"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/athol_fugard_585583",
        "quote": "All of my life had been spent in the shadow of apartheid. And when South Africa went through its extraordinary change in 1994, it was like having spent a lifetime in a boxing ring with an opponent and suddenly finding yourself in that boxing ring with nobody else and realising you've to take the gloves off and get out, and reinvent yourself.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Athol Fugard",
            "url": "/quotes/athol_fugard_585583"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "My Life",
                "url": "/topics/my_life"
            },
            {
                "name": "Through",
                "url": "/topics/through"
            },
            {
                "name": "Reinvent",
                "url": "/topics/reinvent"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/athol_fugard_585576",
        "quote": "I think all of my writing life led up to the writing of 'The Train Driver' because it deals with my own inherited blindness and guilt and all of what being a white South African in South Africa during those apartheid years meant.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Athol Fugard",
            "url": "/quotes/athol_fugard_585576"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "I Think",
                "url": "/topics/i_think"
